  "text": "## Kubernetes Ingress v1beta1 to v1 Migration\n\nThe Ingress API migration from v1beta1 to v1 in Kubernetes involves conversion functions, validation changes (particularly around pathType becoming required), and storage version migration logic.\n\n### Storage Version Configuration\nThe storage version for Ingress is set to **v1** rather than v1beta1. This is configured in `pkg/apis/networking/install/install.go` line 39 via `scheme.SetVersionPriority(v1.SchemeGroupVersion, v1beta1.SchemeGroupVersion)`, indicating that v1 is the preferred/storage version.\n\n### Conversion Chain\nThe conversion between API versions goes through the internal networking API:\n- **v1beta1 → internal networking**: Handled by `Convert_v1beta1_IngressSpec_To_networking_IngressSpec` in `pkg/apis/networking/v1beta1/conversion.go`\n- **v1 → internal networking**: Handled by auto-generated conversion functions in `pkg/apis/networking/v1/zz_generated.conversion.go`\n- **extensions/v1beta1 → internal networking**: Handled by `Convert_v1beta1_IngressSpec_To_networking_IngressSpec` in `pkg/apis/extensions/v1beta1/conversion.go` (for the deprecated extensions API group)\n\n### Ingress Backend Conversion\nBoth v1beta1 (in `pkg/apis/networking/v1beta1/conversion.go`) and extensions/v1beta1 (in `pkg/apis/extensions/v1beta1/conversion.go`) implement manual conversion for IngressBackend:\n- `Convert_v1beta1_IngressBackend_To_networking_IngressBackend`: Converts from the old ServiceName/ServicePort fields to the new Service structure\n- `Convert_networking_IngressBackend_To_v1beta1_IngressBackend`: Performs the reverse conversion\n\nThe conversion maps the legacy ServiceName and ServicePort (IntStr type) fields to the new IngressServiceBackend structure with Name and Port fields.\n\n### HTTPIngressPath Conversion\nAuto-generated conversions in both `pkg/apis/networking/v1/zz_generated.conversion.go` and `pkg/apis/networking/v1beta1/zz_generated.conversion.go` handle HTTPIngressPath conversion, with functions:\n- `Convert_v1_HTTPIngressPath_To_networking_HTTPIngressPath`\n- `Convert_networking_HTTPIngressPath_To_v1_HTTPIngressPath`\n\n### PathType Validation - Key API Change\nThe pathType field became required in v1. The validation is implemented in `pkg/apis/networking/validation/validation.go` at lines 471-472:\n```go\nif path.PathType == nil {\n    return append(allErrs, field.Required(fldPath.Child(\"pathType\"), \"pathType must be specified\"))\n}\n```\n\nThis enforces that every HTTPIngressPath must have pathType explicitly set. The internal types definition in `pkg/apis/networking/types.go` lines 507-535 define the PathType enum with three values:\n- `PathTypeExact`: Matches URL path exactly\n- `PathTypePrefix`: Matches URL path prefix split by '/'\n- `PathTypeImplementationSpecific`: Implementation-specific matching (default)\n\n### Defaults\nThe v1beta1 API provides defaults for pathType in `pkg/apis/networking/v1beta1/defaults.go` line 29, setting it to `PathTypeImplementationSpecific` when not specified, allowing backward compatibility for objects created under v1beta1 rules.\n\n### Type Definitions\nThe internal Ingress types are defined in `pkg/apis/networking/types.go`:\n- `Ingress` struct (line 217): Container for metadata, spec, and status\n- `IngressSpec` struct (line 252): Contains ingressClassName, defaultBackend, TLS, and rules\n- `HTTPIngressPath` struct (line 539): Maps paths to backends with required PathType pointer\n- `PathType` type (line 508): String-based enum for path matching behavior\n\n### Comprehensive Test Coverage\nConversion tests are provided in `pkg/apis/networking/v1beta1/conversion_test.go` to verify bidirectional conversion between v1beta1 and internal networking API versions, ensuring data integrity during the migration process.\n\n### Related Deprecated API\nThe deprecated `extensions/v1beta1` API group also provides Ingress support through conversion functions in `pkg/apis/extensions/v1beta1/conversion.go` and auto-generated code in `pkg/apis/extensions/v1beta1/zz_generated.conversion.go`, maintaining backward compatibility for legacy clients."
}

